  <recipe id="RB-001" category="bread" origin="house" status="production">
    <name>Federal Hill Country Sourdough</name>
    <description>Daily white country loaf, 80% hydration, 24-hour cold retard.</description>
    <yield>4 loaves at 850 g</yield>
    <bakers_percent>
      <ingredient flour="100">King Arthur all-purpose</ingredient>
      <ingredient flour="20">House rye</ingredient>
      <ingredient>Water 80%</ingredient>
      <ingredient>Levain 20%</ingredient>
      <ingredient>Salt 2.2%</ingredient>
    </bakers_percent>
    <process>
      <step time="06:00">Mix and autolyse, 45 minutes</step>
      <step time="07:00">Fold cycle, 3 sets at 30-minute intervals</step>
      <step time="09:00">Pre-shape and bench rest</step>
      <step time="10:00">Final shape, cold retard at 4 C</step>
      <step time="04:00 next day">Score and bake 460 F, 28 minutes</step>
    </process>
    <notes>Bottom shelf of the deck oven runs 10 F hot; rotate at 14 min on that shelf only.</notes>
    <last_edited>2026-10-22</last_edited>
  </recipe>

  <recipe id="PB-014" category="laminated" origin="lyon-trip" status="testing">
    <name>Lyon-Method Butter Croissant</name>
    <description>Imported from the Lyon technique trip, October 20 to 25, 2026. Slower lamination, lower butter overage.</description>
    <yield>32 pieces at 70 g</yield>
    <bakers_percent>
      <ingredient flour="100">King Arthur bread flour</ingredient>
      <ingredient>Water 28%</ingredient>
      <ingredient>Whole milk 22%</ingredient>
      <ingredient>Plugra butter, laminating 54%</ingredient>
      <ingredient>Sugar 11%</ingredient>
      <ingredient>Salt 2%</ingredient>
      <ingredient>Fresh yeast 4.5%</ingredient>
    </bakers_percent>
    <process>
      <step>Detrempe, mix to a low window, 6 minutes</step>
      <step>Cold rest 12 hours at 4 C</step>
      <step>Beurrage, three single turns</step>
      <step>Rest 45 minutes between turns at 4 C</step>
      <step>Roll to 3.5 mm, cut and shape</step>
      <step>Proof 2 hours at 26 C, 70% RH</step>
      <step>Egg wash, bake 410 F convection, 18 minutes</step>
    </process>
    <notes>Lower butter overage than the existing recipe. Lyon teacher: "less butter, more time." Side by side test scheduled Nov 11.</notes>
    <last_edited>2026-11-02</last_edited>
  </recipe>

  <recipe id="PB-022" category="pastry" origin="grandmother" status="production">
    <name>Grandmother Porter's Cinnamon Roll</name>
    <description>Sunday morning roll. Tangzhong base, brown butter cinnamon paste, cream cheese glaze.</description>
    <yield>24 rolls</yield>
    <bakers_percent>
      <ingredient flour="100">All-purpose, King Arthur</ingredient>
      <ingredient>Whole milk 50%</ingredient>
      <ingredient>Tangzhong (slurry) 18%</ingredient>
      <ingredient>Egg 12%</ingredient>
      <ingredient>Sugar 14%</ingredient>
      <ingredient>Plugra butter 12%</ingredient>
      <ingredient>Salt 1.5%</ingredient>
      <ingredient>Yeast 2%</ingredient>
    </bakers_percent>
    <process>
      <step>Tangzhong: cook 5:1 water to flour to a paste, cool</step>
      <step>Knead 9 minutes, ferment 90 minutes</step>
      <step>Roll, spread paste, roll up tight</step>
      <step>Slice and proof 60 minutes</step>
      <step>Bake 365 F, 22 minutes</step>
      <step>Glaze while warm</step>
    </process>
    <notes>From the kitchen on Federal Hill. Grandmother used lard, we use brown butter; flavor reads identical.</notes>
    <last_edited>2025-12-04</last_edited>
  </recipe>

  <recipe id="CK-031" category="custom-cake" origin="house" status="production">
    <name>American Buttercream, House Standard</name>
    <description>Signature finish on every Porter's wedding cake. Plugra-based, no shortening, edible-flower compatible.</description>
    <yield>1.6 kg, covers a three-tier round</yield>
    <bakers_percent>
      <ingredient>Plugra unsalted butter 100%</ingredient>
      <ingredient>Powdered sugar 200%</ingredient>
      <ingredient>Heavy cream 18%</ingredient>
      <ingredient>Vanilla bean paste 4%</ingredient>
      <ingredient>Salt 0.4%</ingredient>
    </bakers_percent>
    <process>
      <step>Whip butter 8 minutes to a pale fluff</step>
      <step>Sift sugar in three additions, scrape between</step>
      <step>Add cream and vanilla on low, then re-whip 4 minutes</step>
      <step>Hold at 18 C; do not refrigerate before piping</step>
    </process>
    <notes>For violets and Federal Hill Flowers' edibles, finish smooth and place flowers within 90 minutes of delivery.</notes>
    <last_edited>2026-02-12</last_edited>
  </recipe>

